name: Biden
summary: Several news articles indicate that there is growing pressure within the Democratic Party for President Biden to withdraw from the presidential race. A recent AP-NORC poll found that nearly two-thirds of Democrats want Biden to step aside, with many expressing concerns about his ability to win against Donald Trump. Congressman Schiff has publicly called on Biden to drop out, warning of a potential wipeout for Democrats if Biden remains in the race. Ashley Judd and Curtis Wilkie have also voiced their support for Biden stepping aside, emphasizing the importance of defeating Trump. Despite these calls, Biden has not yet indicated any plans to withdraw and recently announced his support for major Supreme Court changes. In a prime-time address, Biden urged Americans to reject political violence and work towards unity. However, it remains unclear whether these efforts will be enough to quell the internal dissent within the Democratic Party and sway Biden's decision.

summary: Simone Biles has addressed criticism of her decision to withdraw from events during the Tokyo Olympics, asserting that those who cannot understand her reasons have a personal issue. Looking ahead to the 2024 Paris Games, she is implementing measures such as limiting social media usage. A Netflix documentary explores both her extraordinary talents and her relatable human qualities. The documentary's director discusses working with Biles, her motivations for returning to competition, and her candid reflections on the Tokyo withdrawal. One article highlights a potential rival for Biles in the upcoming Olympics: Brazilian gymnast Rebeca Andrade. Another article praises Biles' response to critics, while another reveals her substantial net worth and how she acquired it through various channels. Eli Lilly has chosen Biles as the face of its Mounjaro commercial campaign. Lastly, a review of the Simone Biles documentary series sheds light on valuable insights gained from the production.
